com.siperian.sif.message.metadata

Class MetaDataHmRelationshipType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.metadata.MetaDataBase
      • com.siperian.sif.message.metadata.MetaDataHmTypeBase
        • com.siperian.sif.message.metadata.MetaDataHmRelationshipType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable

    public class MetaDataHmRelationshipType
extends MetaDataHmTypeBase
    Represents a HM relationship type. HM relationship types determine what types of relationships are available for use on an HM graph.
    See Also:
    MetaDataHmEntityType, DescribeSiperianObjectRequest, Serialized Form

    API Group: Metadata

      • isForEntityTypes

        public boolean isForEntityTypes(String entTypeUid1,
                                String entTypeUid2,
                                boolean allowReverse)
        Determine whether this relationship type applies to the specified entities.
        Parameters:
        entTypeUid1 - The first entity type UID for the relationship type.
        entTypeUid2 - The second entity type UID for the relationship type.
        allowReverse - Specify true if the entity types specified can be in any order in the relationship type. Specify false if the order of entity types in the relationship type has to match the order specified in the method call.
        Returns:
        true if this relationship type can be used for the specified entity types, false otherwise.
